<div class="tw-flex tw-justify-between tw-items-center tw-mb-4">
  <h1 class="ax-page-title tw-flex tw-items-center tw-gap-2"><i class="bi bi-toggles2 tw-text-primary"></i>Configurações de Campo (check-in)</h1>
</div>

<div class="ax-card">
  <div class="ax-card__body">
    <h5 class="tw-font-bold tw-mb-3 tw-flex tw-items-center tw-gap-2">
      <i class="bi bi-geo-alt-fill" style="color:#16a34a"></i>Feature check-in geolocalizado
    </h5>

    <p class="ax-page-subtitle">
      Quando <strong>ativada</strong>, o PWA <code>/field</code> aceita login dos corretores e as rotas <code>/field/*</code> respondem normalmente.
      Quando <strong>desativada</strong>, todas as rotas <code>/field/*</code> retornam 404 e o filtro de check-in
      em <code>/admin/distribution_rules</code> fica inoperante (regras funcionam como antes).
    </p>

    <%= form_with url: admin_field_settings_path, method: :patch, local: true do |f| %>
      <%= ax_switch_field(label: tag.span("Check-in ativado", class: "tw-font-bold"), name: :enabled, value: "1", checked: @enabled, id: "field_enabled", class_name: "tw-mb-4") %>

      <div class="tw-flex tw-justify-end tw-gap-2">
        <%= link_to "Cancelar", admin_root_path, class: "ax-btn ax-btn--ghost" %>
        <%= f.submit "Salvar", class: "ax-btn ax-btn--primary" %>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="ax-card tw-mt-3">
  <div class="ax-card__body">
    <h6 class="tw-font-bold tw-flex tw-items-center tw-gap-2"><i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill" style="color:var(--admin-primary)"></i>Checklist antes de ativar</h6>
    <ul class="tw-text-sm" style="margin-bottom:0">
      <li>Lojas cadastradas em <%= link_to "/admin/stores", admin_stores_path %> com coordenadas, raio e turnos.</li>
      <li>Corretores com <code>field_agent_enabled = true</code> + <code>default_store</code> + turnos vinculados.</li>
      <li>Worker <code>solid_queue</code> rodando com scheduler ativo (cron <code>recurring.yml</code>).</li>
      <li>PostGIS habilitado no Postgres.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
